betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Welcome to Celestial Journey. This pack is a spiritual succesor to the "Divine Journey" modpack.

This questbook is broken into 13 chapters representing a linear progression through numerous mods. You will have to jump between the different chapters to progress. 

Â§l
No Description

This is where it all begins. Punch trees until you get at least 10 wood.

Note: This modpack has OreExcavation which allows you to break numerous logs by holding down the grave key (by default).
The crafting station holds your items in place even after exiting.
Make yourself a wooden pickaxe.
Now that you have a pickaxe, mine at least 9 pieces of coal.
Are you out mining but you've run out of wood? With the addition of stone torches this is no longer a problem! Make 10 of them.
Make yourself some chests.
Now that you have a pickaxe, mine at least 8 pieces of cobblestone.
Craft an oak basic drawer.
Craft a furnace.
Craft an iron drawer upgrade .
Craft a stone pickaxe.
Find and collect iron ore to produce some ingots.

Craft a pattern chest.

Note: the chest can be collected without dropping its contents.
Ha, get it?... I'll stop.
Mine at least 6 pieces of redstone.
Make some blank patterns.
Craft a golden drawer upgrade.
Craft an obsidian drawer upgrade.
Craft a diamond drawer upgrade.
Craft an emerald drawer upgrade.
Craft a tool station, a stencil table and a part builder.
Get some charged certus quartz.
Mine some diamonds.
Craft a charger.
Create a meteorite compass to find meteorites.
Once you have found a meteorite, mine some skystone.
You can find an inscriber logic press inside a meteorite.
You can find an inscriber calculation press inside a meteorite.
You can find an inscriber engineering press inside a meteorite.
You can find an inscriber silicon press inside a meteorite.
Make a tool forge. This allows you to craft advanced tools.
Make a stirling generator to generate RF by burning solid fuels.
Smelt your grout to get seared brick.
Combine your collected gravel, sand and clay to craft grout.
Use your seared brick to create some seared bricks.
Everything you need to get started with your smeltery.

Make 5 crystal growth accelerators and use them to make pure certus quartz. You can do so by sorrounding a water source block and throwing certus quartz seeds in it. 

You need to power the crystal growth accelerators with ME conduits, through an energy acceptor.
Use your inscriber to create some printed silicon.
Craft an inscriber.

Craft a caster's gauntlet.

The gauntlet is used on a runic matrix to start infusions. It can also be used to cast spells.
Craft a machine frame.
Craft a casting table and casting basin.
Make a basic redstone furnace.
Craft a simple machine chassis.
Craft a SAG Mill to grind ores and other items.
An alloy smelter is used to both smelt items and create alloys.
Craft a basic pulverizer to double your ore output.
Use the alloy smelter to create dark steel.

Mine some obsidian.

Note: Did you know we have vein miner in this pack?

Craft an item output port.

It can be used in the construction of a heat exchanger, allowing items to be extracted from the structure.

Craft a heat exchanger.

At least 1 is needed in the construction of the heat exchanger multiblock.
The heart of the heat exchanger. Craft a heat exchanger controller.

Craft a heating chamber.

At least 1 is needed in the construction of a syngas producer.
Use the alloy smelter to make some redstone alloy.

Craft a fluid output valve.

It can be used in the construction of a heat exchanger and syngas producer.

Craft a fluid intake valve.

It can be used in the construction of a heat exchanger, gas turbine, steam turbine and syngas producer.
Throw a charged certus quartz crystal, nether quartz and redstone in water to create 2 fluix crystals.
Make some silicon.
Use an inscriber to make a printed engineering circuit.
Use an inscriber to make an engineering processor.
Craft a quibit cell.
Use an alloy smelter to make some electrical steel ingots.
Use an inscriber to make a printed logic circuit.
Use an inscriber to make a logic processor.

Craft a ME controller.

The ME controller has the ability to transmit data throughout the ME Network using 32 channels per side. The ME dense cable is the only cable that can support 32 channel simultaneously. 

A multiblock structure can be made consisting out of multiple adjacent ME controller blocks.
Use an inscriber to make a printed calculation circuit.
Use an inscriber to make a calculation processor.
Craft a basic card.
The Vat can produce various liquids from combining 2 items and a fluid that differs for each.
Craft an annihilation core.
Craft a 1k ME Storage Component
Craft a formation core.
Craft a 4k ME storage component.
Craft a ME import bus.
Craft a ME terminal.
Craft a ME export bus.
Craft a ME drive. This allows you to store up to 10 ME storage cells.
Craft a wireless terminal. To use this, link it to your ME system through a ME security terminal.
Craft a machine case.
Craft a ME crafting terminal.

Craft a ME pattern terminal.

This allows you to encode blank patterns into encoded patterns. There are 2 modes: crafting patterns and processing patterns.
Craft a ME fluid terminal.
Craft a ME acceleration card. You can use multiple acceleration cards in a machine to increase its speed even further.
Craft a 16k ME storage component.
Craft an octadic capacitor. It can be added to Ender IO machines to increase their processing speed even more.
Craft a crafting card. The card allows ME network devices to draw on the ME auto crafting system when items run out of stock by placing automatic job orders.
Craft an advanced card.
Craft a 64k ME storage component.
Craft a 256k ME storage component.
The drawer controller can coordinate the function of all connected drawers within a 12 block radius.
Craft a double-layer capacitor. It can be added to Ender IO machines to increase their processing speed.
Make a crafting unit. This item is used to make the crafting CPU.

Craft a ME level emitter. 

It can be used to indicate either the level of a specified item or the ME Network energy level. It can be set to emit a redstone signal if you have less or more of a specific item than the specified amount, which can then be used to trigger autocrafting.

Make a molecular assembler. 

To use it, place it next to an ME interface that touches your ME system. Then create patterns in a pattern terminal and put it in the ME interface either manually or through an interface terminal.

Craft a ME interface.

It allows the ME Network to interact with machines, transport pipes and tubes. You can configure certain items to be exported from the ME network and it will import the output from machines and transport systems. 

It is also used together with the automated crafting feature of the ME network.

Craft a ME interface terminal. 

With this terminal you can view what items you have stored in your ME interfaces throughout your system, so you don't have look though all of them to find something.
Craft a ME storage bus. This item can be used to connect external storage (e.g. chests and drawers) to your ME system, and the items inside them will be treated as if they were in your ME system.
Craft a ME IO port. It lets you transfers item between your ME network and your storage cells.
Craft a basic capacitor.
Use an alloy smelter to make some energetic alloy ingots.

Craft a cell workbench. 

This allows you to rename and format an ME storage cell to specify the items' data it will store.

Craft a view cell. 

This allows you to filter the items viewed in the different ME network terminals.
Craft some enhanced energy conduits.
Craft some energy conduits.
Craft some ender energy conduits.
Use an alloy smelter or an induction smelter to make some conductive iron ingots.

Use an alloy smelter or an induction smelter to make some vibrant alloy ingots.

Note: you will need a lot of these later on, so making an enderman spawner might be useful.
Use an induction smelter or an alloy smelter to make some soularium ingots.
A soul binder allows you to change the type of a broken spawner by binding it with a filled soul vial.

Make a Slice'N'Splice. 

The Slice'N'Splice requires two tools in order to function: an axe and shears. It is recommended to start off with dark steel (you can replace them later with even better ones).
Use an alloy smelter or an inductive smelter to make some pulsating iron ingots.

Make a Crafter tier 1. 

It can be used to craft multiple items independent from each other or else it can be used for more complicated multi-step crafting recipes.
Make a Crafter tier 2 if you need more crafting space.
Make a Crafter tier 3 if you need even more crafting space.
Make an induction smelter.
Make a magma crucible.
Make a fluid transposer.

Craft a basic capacitor bank. 

It is a shapeless multiblock; putting a basic capacitor bank next to another basic capacitor bank will combine their energy storage (same goes for the capacitor bank and vibrant capacitor bank).
Craft a capacitor bank.
Craft a vibrant capacitor bank.
Get it? Okay... I'll really stop this time.
Make some bronze ingots.
Use an alloy smelter to make some enderium ingots.
Craft a Lexica Botania.
Craft a blood altar. Make sure you place this somewhere with enough space, as a fully sized (tier 5) altar is 19x19.

Make a weak blood orb using the blood altar. To use the orb, you must bind it to yourself by right-clicking while holding the orb. 

If your place your blood orb in the blood altar, you can fill up your own internal soul network. Alternatively, you can right-click it (adding 200 LP) to fill it up using your own health.
Use the blood altar to create some blank slates out of frozen stone from Iceika. You can also use end stone or twilight stone.

Make an apprentice blood orb using the blood altar. To use the orb, you must bind it to yourself by right-clicking while holding the orb. 

This blood orb allows you to store more LP in your internal soul network and is used to craft higher tier items.
Craft an alchemy table.
Craft a lava crystal. This item is mainly used as a crafting component, but - when bound to yourself - can also be used as a replacement fuel source in furnaces (draining 25 LP per operation).
Make a magician blood orb using the blood altar.

Make an earth inscription tool. 

This is used to construct rituals. To use it, bound it to yourself by right-clicking while holding the inscription tool.

Make a water inscription tool. 

This is used to construct rituals. To use it, bound it to yourself by right-clicking while holding the inscription tool.

Make a fire inscription tool. 

This is used to construct rituals. To use it, bound it to yourself by right-clicking while holding the inscription tool.

Make an air inscription tool. 

This is used to construct rituals. To use it, bound it to yourself by right-clicking while holding the inscription tool.

Use an alchemy table to make a simple stimulant.

Note: you will need Â§la lotÂ§lÂ§lÂ§r of these.
Use an alchemy table to make an advanced stimulant. This is an upgraded version of the simple stimulant.
Craft a weak activation crystal. Bind it to yourself by right-clicking while holding the item. This allows you to activate rituals (excluding grand rituals) using your own life essence.
Make a master blood orb using the blood altar.
Use an alchemy table to make some solis.

Use an alchemy table to make some vitriol. 

Note: Vitriol requires a cyclops eye, so once you can make offensa, a powered spawner for cyclopses may be a good idea.
Use an alchemy table to make some carbo.
Use an alchemy table to make some defensio.
Use an alchemy table to make some ambustio.
Use an alchemy table to make some offensio. Now you can make Ender IO powered spawners!
Use an alchemy table to make some aquis.
Use an alchemy table to make some glacialis.
Use an alchemy table to make some aeris.
Use the blood altar to create some reinforced slates.

Craft a transposition sigil using an alchemy array.

It allows you to store and recall a block at the cost of 5000 LP.
Craft some blank runes. These are used in upgrading the tier of the blood altar and in crafting other runes.
Craft a hellfire forge. This is needed to craft recipes requiring Will and to fill tartaric gems.

Use a hellfire forge to create arcane ashes. 

This is used to create the alchemy array (needed to craft sigils).

Craft a divination sigil using an alchemy array. 

It allows you to check the current amount of life essence  in the blood altar and inside your own personal network.
Craft some self sacrifice runes.
Use the blood altar to create some demonic slates.
Use the blood altar to create some ethereal slates.

Craft some speed runes. 

These provides an additive 20% increase to the processing speed of the blood altar.

Craft some runes of sacrifice. These will increase the total amount of LP gained by sacrificing mobs with a dagger of sacrifice by an additive 10%.

Eventually, you can setup the well of suffering and the regeneration ritual and use mobs to continously generate life essence.
Craft some runes of augmented capacity. These add 10% extra LP.

Craft some runes of the orb. 

These add an additional 2% capacity per rune to blood orb storage potential.
Craft some displacement runes.

Craft an air sigil using an alchemy array. 

Bind it to yourself by right-clicking when holding the sigil. After this, you will be able to launch yourself in the direction you're looking at while right-clicking (at the cost of 50 LP per click).

Note: you still take fall damage.
Use the blood altar to create some imbued slates.

Craft a sigil of the blood lamp using an alchemy array. 

It allows you to create a blood light anywhere by right-clicking a block (consuming 10 LP).

Craft a teleposition sigil using an alchemy array. 

It teleports you to the linked teleposer (shift-right click the teleposer with the sigil to link it).
Make some empty sockets.
Use a blood altar to fill up your empty sockets.

Make some binding reagent using a hellfire forge. 

This is used to make bound tools and living armour.

Craft all bound tools.

The tools have an active and inactive mode that can be toggled between by shift-right clicking them.

Killing mobs with a bound blade (at the cost of LP) drops weak blood shards, which are used to upgrade the blood altar to tier 4 and are used in various crafting recipes.

The bound pickaxe, shovel and axe have an ability called 'beast mode': holding right-click will charge the tool and break a 11x11x11 area, at the cost of 10 000 LP.
Create all pieces of the living armor.
Craft some awakened activation crystals.
Make some crystal clusters to upgrade your blood altar to tier 6.
Make a transcendent blood orb using a tier 6 blood altar.
Craft a demon gem.
Make a archmage blood orb using a blood altar. This requires terrasteel.

Corrupted shards can be obtained from killing Enthralled Dramcryxes and The Grue's, that roam around at very low elevations in the overworld. 

Note: you might want to create a powered spawner for these later on.
Molten shards can be obtained from killing Hell Spiders and Wildfires, that roam around in the Nether.
Go to the Nether.

Kill some blazes. 

As you progress throughout the pack you will need to visit this questline more and more often as you need a lot of items from different dimensions.
Craft the call of the Watcher to summon the Watcher in the Nether.
Go to the End.
Craft a mysterious clock.

Eden is the first Twilight dimension you will go to. 

Note: Don't forget to bring a jetpack.

Note: If you're low on eden fragments, consider using a powered spawner for mobs that drop Eden souls.
Craft some divine rocks to make a portal (in the same shape as a Nether portal) to Eden.
Craft a twilight clock. This item allows you enter all 5 Twilight dimensions: Eden, Wildwood, Apalachia, Skythern and Mortum.

The Wildwood is the second Twilight dimension you will go to. Collect some Wildwood fragments to be able to progress into the next Twilight dimension, Apalachia.

Note: if you're not strong enough to survive here yet, progress further in other magic mods first.
Apalachia is the third Twilight dimension you will go to. Collect Apalachia fragments to be able to continue to Skythern.
Skythern is the fourth Twilight dimension you will go to. Collect enough Skythern fragments to be able to continue to Mortum.

The Mortun Depths is the fifth and final Twilight dimension you will go to. 

You need mortum blocks to create a nightmare bed (the portal).
Collect some draconium dust from the End.
Make some infused heart soup.
Craft 12 Arcana portal frames to be able to create the portal to the dungeon of Arcana.
Kill mobs from the Dungeon of Arcana to obtain collector fragments.

Find Lord Vatticus in the Dungeon of Arcana and trade 16 collectors for a charged collector.

Â§c

Kill dungeon constructors to obtain dungeon keys. Use them to open doors in the Dungeon of Arcana where you will find arcanium ore.

Find an arcanium extractor and place arcanium in the top slot and charged collectors in the bottom slot to smelt arcanium ore into arcanium.
Find Datticon in the Dungeon of Arcana and trade arcanium for elevantium.
Find Datticon in the Dungeon of Arcana and trade arcanium for acceleron.
Obtain fire crystals found in Vethea.
Make your way to the top layer of Vethea to obtain firelights.

Make your way to the top layer of Vethea and kill mobs to obtain shiny pearls.

Note: it is recommended to create a powered spawner for these mobs.

Craft a nightmare bed and enter Vethea.

Note: your inventory does not transfer with you to Vethea.
Craft a golden fury. This is the item you need to craft the Bound Blade from Blood Magic.
Summon and defeat the King of Scorchers in the Nether. Once killed, he will drop fury fire.
Craft an infernal flame. This is used to summon the King of Scorchers.

Purple blaze can be obtained from killing scorchers (they look like purple blazes). 

Note: you might want to create a powered spawner to automatically spawn these, as you will need to defeat the King of Scorchers multiple times.

Now that you're able to make energetic alloys, it is time to visit the Twilight Forest. 

Make a 2 x 2 pool of water and surround this with flowers, then throw an energetic alloy in it to create the portal.
Craft a blank magic map. This allows you to map the surrounding area while in the Twilight Forest.
Find the Naga in the Naga Courtyard and kill it. Claim it's trophy.
Find the Twilight Lich in the Lich Tower and kill it. Claim it's trophy.
Find a maze map focus (most likely to be found in various chests in a Labyrinth) and use it to craft a blank maze map.
Find the Minoshroom in Labyrinths (found in the swamp biome) and kill it. Claim the Meef Stroganoff.
Find the Hydra in the Hydra Lair in the middle of a Fire Swamp and kill it. Claim it's trophy.

Enter the Dark Forest and find the Goblin Knight Stronghold. Find a room with a trophy pedestal and place any trophy you've previously earned on it to remove the shield around the stronghold.

Defeat Knights inside to obtain armor shards. This item is used to create knightmetal, which is needed in some lategame recipes. 

Once inside the stronghold, find and kill the Knight Phantom to get access to the Dark Tower.
Find the Ur-Ghast in the Dark Tower in the middle of the Dark Forest and kill it. Claim it's trophy.
Find the Alpha Yeti in the Yeti Lair in the center of Snowy Forests and kill it. Claim it's fur.
Find the Snow Queen in the Aurora Palace in Glacier biomes and kill her. Claim her trophy.
Find the Troll Cave beneath the Highlands. Kill the Troll and loot the vault to obtain magic beans and uberous soil.
Obtain 3 wither skeleton skulls.
Spawn and kill the wither.
Find the Giant's Twilight Cloud Cottage above the Twilight Highlands biome. Plant magic beans on uberous soil to be able to climb up to the cloud. Kill the Giant Miner and obtain it's giant pickaxe.

Find the giant obsidian vault in the Mushroom Vault of a Troll Cave and break it using the giant pickaxe to obtain the Lamp of Cinders. Use the Lamp of Cinders to burn down some thorns in the Thorns biome to get acces to the Thornlands.

Obtain some castle bricks from the Castle inside the Thorns biome.

Note: OreExcavation is your friend.

Obtain some castle roof tiles from the Castle inside the Thorns biome.

Note: Again, OreExcavation is your friend.
Craft a snow globe. This item is used to light the portal to the first DivineRPG dimension: Iceika.

Create a portal out of snow blocks and light it with a snow globe to be able to go to Iceika. Once you're there, get some frozen stone.

Note: OreExcavation is your friend.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Toss a coin to your Witcher
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Kill 150 zombies, 150 skeletons and 75 creepers.

Craft a powered spawner. 

To use it, combine it with a broken spawner in an anvil to set the type of mob it will spawn. You can change a broken spawner's type by combining it with a soul vial of the desired mob in a soul binder.

Note: you will need a bat and enderman spawner to craft more powered spawners.

Make a petal apothecary. 

This is used to create all functional flowers. To do so, fill it with water, throw some petals in and then throw in a seed to finalize the process. 

Note: don't forget to automate it.
Use an alchemy table to make some potestas.
Obtain inferium essence.
Craft an inferium seed.
Craft an inferior infusion crystal to be able to make prudentium essence.
Craft prudentium essence. This allows you to start making many mystical crops.
Craft a prudentium infusion crystal to be able to make intermedium essence.
Craft some water seeds.
Craft intermedium essence.
Craft some redstone seeds.
Craft some sheep seeds.
Craft an intermediate infusion crystal to be able to make superium essence.
Craft some copper seeds.
Craft some quicksilver seeds.
Craft superium essence.
Craft some enderman seeds.
Craft some lapis lazuli seeds.
Craft some iron seeds.
Craft a superium infusion crystal to be able to make the crÃ¨me de la crÃ¨me of essences: supremium essence.
That what is forbidden for alchemists. Craft some gold seeds.
The true superior essence. Craft some supremium essence.
Craft some mass supremium essence blocks.
Craft some wither skeleton seeds.
Craft a master infusion crystal. This has unlimited uses.
Craft some enderium seeds.
Craft some dark steel seeds.
Craft some redstone alloy seeds.
Craft some draconium seeds.

Craft a farming station.

To make it work, you need to power this machine, give it a hoe and an axe, and put it in the center of your farm. The farming station will automatically harvest, collect, and replant all crops and trees in its range. The range can be upgraded using capacitors.

Note: doesn't work with AgriCraft crops.
Craft some terrasteel seeds.
Craft some death bases.
Craft a corrupted base.
Craft a creative flux pack.
Craft a creative jetpack.
Craft a creative flux capacitor
Craft a creative energy cell.
Craft a creative resevoir.
Craft a creative capacitor bank.
Craft a creative drum.
Craft a reactor creative coolant port.
Craft some crop sticks. You can put all types of seeds on crop sticks to turn them into AgriCraft seeds. This has as advantage that you can make the attributes of the seed better.

Craft a clipper. 

The clipper allows you to chop plant-parts off of an AgriCraft crop, to gain clippings. These can be planted again, and will retain the attributes of the seed it was clipped off of.
Craft a seed analyzer.

Craft an imaginary time block. 

This allows you to increase the tick rate of the crops around the machine.

Craft a plant sower. 

This machine is used to automatically plant seeds in farmland above the machine. The range of the plant sower can be expanded with a range addon.

Craft a plant gatherer. 

This machine is used to harvest both crops and trees, producing sludge as a byproduct. The range of the plant gatherer can be expanded with a range addon.

Craft a pure daisy. 

This flower is (mainly) used to convert wood and stone into livingwood and livingrock respectively. The conversion process takes 60 seconds.

Note: don't forget to automate this.

Craft a leadstone flux capacitor.

Capacitor need to be fully charged to complete the quest.
Craft a hardened flux capacitor.
Craft a reinforced flux capacitor.
Craft a signalum flux capacitor.
Craft a resonant flux capacitor.
Craft a leadstone thruster.
Craft a hardened thruster.
Craft a reinforced thruster.
Craft a fluxed thruster.
Craft a resonant thruster.
Craft a leadstone jetpack.
Craft a hardened jetpack.
Craft a reinforced jetpack.
Craft a flux-infused jetplate.
Craft a resonant jetpack.
Craft a conductive iron thruster.
Craft an electrical steel thruster.
Craft an energetic thruster.
Craft a vibrant thruster.
Craft a dark soularium thruster.
Craft a conductive iron jetpack.
Craft an electrical steel jetpack.
Craft an energetic jetpack.
Craft a vibrant jetpack.
Craft a dark soularium jetplate.
Craft an iron chest.
Craft a gold chest.
Craft a diamond chest.
Craft an obsidian chest. It has the same inventory space as a diamond chest, but is completely blast resistant.
Craft a crystal chest. It has the same inventory space as a diamond chest, but the items inside are visible without opening the chest.

Craft a vector plate. 

The vector plate pushes mobs in the direction of the arrows (about 2 blocks per second), however sneaking mobs are not effected.
Craft a fast vector plate.

One of many traps. 

When an entity stands on the player trap, it will do player damage. Mobs killed with this trap will drop EXP and player only mob drops.
Make a builder. Select an area to mine with a shape card (quarry), and put it inside the builder.
Craft a basic shape card.

Craft a shape card (silk quarry). 

This mines resources with the effect of silk touch.

Craft a shape card (fortune quarry). 

This mines resources with the effect of fortune III.

Craft a shape card (quarry). 

Use this with RF Tools' builder to mine out an area of land automatically.

Craft a soul vial.

Right-clicking a mob with a soul vial will put the mob in it.
Craft a control circuit.
The heart of the syngas producer. Craft a syngas producer controller.

Craft a mixing chamber. 

At least 1 is needed in the construction of a syngas producer.

Craft an item input port.

It can be used in the construction of a syngas producer, allowing item input.
The heart of the steam turbine generator multiblock. Craft a steam turbine controller.

Craft an iron turbine. 

It can be used in the construction of a gas turbine and a steam turbine, and produces up to 100 RF/t.
The heart of the gas turbine. Craft a gas turbine controller.
Craft a forge energy emitter.

Craft a fuel tank. 

It can be used in the construction of a gas turbine, increasing maximum intake tank by 16.000 mb.

Craft a fuel/air mixer.

It can be used in the gas turbine structure, increasing its fuel efficiency to 135%.

Craft a gas mix compressor. 

It can be used in the gas turbine structure, increasing its fuel efficiency to 185%. It only works if a fuel/air mixer is installed in the same structure.

Craft a basic power capacitor. 

It can be used in the construction of a gas turbine and a steam turbine.

Craft an advanced power capacitor. 

It can be used in the construction of a gas turbine and a steam turbine.

Craft a sensor module. 

It can check for different conditions on the machine and emit a redstone signal when a condition is met.

Craft a redstone control unit. 

This gives you control of various processes inside machines using a redstone signal.
Make some reactor casing blocks.
Craft a reactor fuel rod.

Craft a reactor access port.

It is the only way to get fuel into the reactor and waste products out of the reactor. The port has two modes: input and output.

Craft a reactor redstone port.

It can be used as either an input or an output to allow for greater control of a reactor. Its GUI is accessed by right-clicking on it.
Craft a reactor controller.

Craft a reactor control rod.

Once you have built the reactor, you can change with what percentage the rods are increased with to generate more or less power. This way, you can conserve energy.
Craft a reactor redstone flux power tap.
Craft a steam dynamo.
Craft a magmatic dynamo.
Craft a compression dynamo.
Craft a reactant dynamo.
Craft an enervation dynamo.
Craft a numismatic dynamo.

Craft an augment: turbine conversion.

A steam dynamo with a turbine conversion installed generates RF using steam instead of water and solid fuel.

Craft an augment: isentropic reservoir.

An installed isentropic reservoir quadruples the maximum power output of a magmatic dynamo, and increases the amount of RF it generates from each unit of fuel by 15%.

Craft an augment: ignition plugs.

An installed ignition plugs augment quadruples the maximum power output of a compression dynamo, and increases the amount of RF it generates from each unit of fuel by 50%.

Craft an augment: elemental catalyzer.

An installed elemental catalyzer quintuples the maximum power output of a reactant dynamo, and increases the amount of RF it generates from each reaction by 25%.

Craft an augment: disjunctive extraction.

An installed disjunctive extraction augment quintuples the maximum power output of an enervation dynamo.

Craft an augment: lapidary calibration.

An installed lapidary calibration augment allows for a numismatic dynamo to use various gemstones as fuel. It also quintuples the dynamoâs maximum power output, and increases the amount of RF it generates from each unit of fuel by 25%.
Make some electrum ingots.
Make some signalum ingots.
Make some lumium ingots.
Make 8 pieces of livingwood.
Make 8 pieces of livingrock.

Craft a wand of the forest. 

This allows you rotate mana spreaders, check the mana stored in a mana pool and check the progress of a botanical brewery.

Craft a horn of the forest. 

When blowing into the horn, grass, flowers and crops will be harvested in a 25 x 25 x 7 area around you.

Craft a mana spreader.

It is used to transport mana. If the target of the spreader is a block that can contain mana, and if it isn't full, the spreader will fire a mana burst, which will travel to the target, and pass the mana along to it.
Obtain dreamwood by throwing livingwood through a portal to Alfheim.
Craft an elven gateway core and setup the portal to alfheim.

Make some terrasteel. 

Terrasteel is created via an infusion ritual atop a terrestrial agglomeration plate. To form a terrasteel ingot, throw a manasteel ingot, a mana pearl, and a mana diamond onto the plate. The plate then must receive 500,000 mana (sparks are the best way to do this) without any of the 3 items being picked up.

Craft a terrestrial agglomeration plate.

This allows you to craft terrasteel.
Create some manasteel. This is one of the most basic resources in Botania.

Craft a mana pool.

It is used to store the mana produced by flowers. Throwing resources in the mana pool will cause them to get infused with mana, turning them into more powerful forms.
Craft some mana diamonds.
Make some mana infused strings.
Craft some mana pearls.

Craft an endoflame.

It is a very basic generating flower: it will absorb any combustible items/blocks dropped next to it and burn through them to generate mana while the fuel lasts.

Craft a hydroangeas.

It generates mana by consuming water source blocks in a 3 x 3 area around it. Consuming a source block will power it for 2 seconds. The hydroangeas will however wither and turn into a dead bush after being placed for 1 hour.

Craft a runic altar.

When provided with mana through mana spreaders and when the correct items are placed onto the altar, it will craft runes for you. 

To complete crafting, right-click or throw a livingrock on top of the altar, then use the wand of the forest.

Note: Try to automate this (with automatic mana production, droppers or open crates, and mechanical users).
Make a rune of mana.
Make a rune of water.
Make a rune of fire.
Make a rune of earth
Make a rune of air
Make a rune of winter.
Make a rune of spring.
Make a rune of summer.
Make a rune of autumn.
Make a rune of gluttony.
Make a rune of greed.
Make a rune of pride.
Make a rune of sloth.

Craft a ring of magnetization. 

When worn in the baubles ring slot, any items in a 13 x 13 area around you will be pulled towards you. Solegnolia flowers will prevent this ring from pulling items inside its range, as well as blocking the rings of players in its range.

Craft a greater ring of magnetization.

This is an upgrade of the ring of magnetization, increasing the affected range to a 33 x 33 area around you.
Obtain dragonstone by throwing mana diamonds through the portal to Alfheim.
Obtain elementium by throwing two manasteel ingots through the portal to Alfheim.
Craft 4 gaia pylons.
Summon the guardian of gaia by shift-right clicking a terrasteel ingot on an active beacon with 4 gaia pylons nearby.
Craft a gaia spirit ingot.

Craft a gaia mana spreader.

The gaia mana spreader can fire mana bursts up to 48 blocks before suffering mana loss.

Summon a harder guardian of gaia by shift-right clicking a gaia spirit ingot on an active beacon with 4 gaia pylons nearby.

This gaia guardian will always drop a dice of fate. This item can either be used for crafting or right clicked to receive one of the 6 botania relics.
Obtain pixie dust by throwing mana pearls through the portal to Alfheim.

Craft a kekimurus.

Every 4 seconds, the flower attempts to consume one slice of cake in an 11 x 11 x 11 area around itself, producing 1,800 mana per slice, resulting in 10,800 per cake.

Craft a entropinnyum.

It generates mana by absorbing primed TNT entities in a 12 block range immediately before they explode, producing 6,500 mana per explosion.

Craft a thermalily.

It generates mana by consuming lava. After consuming a block of lava, a thermalily will produce 20 mana per tick for 900 ticks (producing a total of 18,000 mana), then go on cooldown for 6,000 ticks (5 minutes).

Craft a hopperhock.

This flower will pick up items around it and has a default range of 6 blocks which can be increased to 10 when supplied with mana.
Craft some manaweave cloth.
Craft a mana pylon.

Craft a mana tablet.

It is a portable object which can carry mana on itself. Dropping a mana tablet on a mana pool will allow it to transfer mana from one to the other.

Note: it seems to be immune to the ring of magnetization.

Craft a band of mana.

When worn in the baubles slot, the band of mana is able to store mana like the mana tablet. It can store 500,000 mana.
Use an alchemy table to make some saxum.
Use an alchemy table to make some terrestris.
Right-click a bookshelf with salis mundus to create the Thaumonomicon.
Craft some salis mundus.
Right-click a crafting table with salis mundus to create an arcane workbench (pick it up to complete this quest).
Right-click a cauldron with salis mundus to create a crucible (pick it up to complete this quest).

Craft the goggles of revealing.

It allows you to see amounts of stored essentia and flux rifts through walls. It also provides a vis discount of 5% when crafting.

Right-click a wood table with filled scribing tools to create a research table (pick it up to complete this quest).

It is used to obtain theories. It consumes paper, ink from scribing tools, and inspiration.

Craft a thaumometer.

It is primarily used to scan blocks and items to unlock new research topics, complete research topics, and gain observation points in areas of study. Right-clicking with it when looking at an object highlighted in blue sparkles will add points to observation.
Craft some enchanted fabric.
Craft the thaumaturge armor set to give you vis discounts.

Craft a thaumic dioptra.

It shows the levels of vis and flux for the surrounding chunks. The default view is vis, and if you right click it, then it will show flux.

Craft 2 pieces of yellow nitor.

When put under a crucible it will heat up the water. It is also used in various crafting recipes.

Craft a focal manipulator.

It is used to imbue a focus with spells that can be cast with a caster's gauntlet.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Why be Harry Potter when you can be Thanos?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a caster's gauntlet.

The gauntlet's main use is casting spells stored on casting foci by the focal manipulator. It can be also used on a runic matrix to start infusions.
Throw an ordo shard in a crucible to get a blank lesser focus.

Craft a blank advanced focus.

It is designed to be used in a caster's gauntlet and has a complexity cap of 25 points. You can modify or add effects to it using a focal manipulator.

Craft a blank greater focus.

It is designed to be used in a caster's gauntlet and has a complexity cap of 50 points. You can modify or add effects to it using a focal manipulator.

Craft an essentia smeltery and an arcane alembic.

The smeltery is used to disassemble items and blocks into essentia. Use some sort of fuel, e.g. coal, to power it (alumentum works best).

Place an arcane alembic on top of the essentia smeltery eject essentia into it. The essentia can then be extracted out of an alembic using jars or more complex means.

Craft some alumentum.

If used as an essentia smeltery fuel, it increases the smelting speed by 20%.

Craft a focus pouch.

It is able to carry 18 different foci.

Craft an arcane bellow.

Bellows placed on the side of a smeltery will greatly increase the heat it generates, allowing items to be broken down into a slurry much quicker.

Craft an auxiliary slurry pump and venting port.

You can place a slurry pump on any side of your smeltery and it will act as a second output - outputting to the arcane alembics above it.

When attached to the side of an essentia smeltery, an auxiliary venting port decreases the amount of flux that is let into the surrounding area. You can add up to three vents, but they do have diminishing returns (adding 2 would be most efficient).

Craft a filling and emptying essentia transfuser.

The filling essentia transfuser is used to transport essentia without using essentia tubes to warded jars within 16 blocks from the essentia container that it is attached to, including arcane alembics and essentia centrifuges.

The emptying essentia transfuser is used to transport essentia from warded jars within 16 blocks into the device that it is attached to, such as the thaumatorium.
Make an infusion altar.

1:10.command:8:
#Script Comment
say Running reward script...
/thaumcraft research @p INFUSION

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft some warded jars.

It stores up to 250 units of any one type of essentia. It can also be labeled to restrict the jar to a specific kind of essentia even when empty.

Craft a void jar.

Void jars can be used to delete the excess essentia (use a label to only void the type indicated).

Craft an infusion speed and cost stone.

The infusion speed stone decreases the duration of infusion recipes but increases the cost. The infusion cost stone on the other hand reduces costs, while increasing the duration. 

The infusion speed or cost stone must be placed below each pillar of the altar.

Put two alchemical constructs on top of a crucible and right-click it with salis mundus to create the thaumatorium. 

The thaumatorium will automatically pull out the requires essentia from any jars that are hooked up to it. All you need to do for the thaumatorium to work is to make sure that it's constantly full of catalysts and has enough essentia.

Craft some tallow candles.

These can be used to stabilize you infusion altar.

Craft a stabilizer and redstone inlay.

Stabilizers need to be placed the same way as candles or skulls. 

A redstone inlay is used to connect stabilizers with arcane pedestals to prevent items from being knocked off pedestals. They also provide a slight stabilizing bonus, so placing them around the infusion altar in a symmetrical fashion is recommended.

Craft an arcane spa.

Some stages will give you warp when you complete them. Warp is not good, and can have some very strange side effects. 

Using soap is a chore, so craft the spa, pump water into it and fill it with bath salts. This will then fill a 5x5 area with water. This way, you can hop in and hop out without having to wash yourself with soap.
Make some magic tallow.

Craft a mnemonic matrix.

By attaching a mnemonic matrix to to the side of a thaumatorium, the amount of remembered active recipes is increased by 2.
Make some alchemical brass ingots.
Make some thaumium ingots.

Create some void seeds.

It is dropped by collapsing flux rifts or created by void siphons draining nearby flux rifts.
Make some void metal ingots.
Craft the thaumium armor set.

Craft the thaumium fortress armor set.

When worn as a set, it provides the same protection as diamond armor, but with the added benefit of providing extra magical damage resistance and having a much higher durability.

Craf the void thaumaturge armor set.

This set will give you vis discount depending on your level of warp, goggles of revealing in the hood, and you will gain temporary warp that could turn into permanent warp.
Make a golem press.

Why do anything when you can have golems do all the work.

Seals are placed into the world and then configured with the golemancerâs bell
Craft a 1k essentia storage component.
Craft a 4k essentia storage component.
Craft a 16k essentia storage component.
Craft a 64k essentia storage component.
Craft a ME essentia terminal.
Craft an arcane crafting terminal.
Collect 10 belladonna seeds. These are commonly found in tall grass.
Collect 10 garlic seeds. These can be obtained from alliums.
Collect 10 mandrake seeds. These are found in grass.
Collect 10 white sage seeds. These can be found in dead bushes.

Craft a witches' oven.

It is used to distill saplings and other items into basic fumes.
Make some adroysium.
Make some arcane adroysium.
Make an adroysium ingot.
Make some oak spirit, birch soul, spruce heart, cloudy oil and acacia resin.

Setup the witches' altar (see its tooltip).

To gain Magical Energy (ME), you must place flora near your altar. Altars can only efficiently extract ME from flora from those within approximately 8 blocks of it, but can extract ME from flora within a 32x32 radius. You can offset this by having a variety of trees, however.

After this, place a (filled) goblet, diamond sword, blaze/end rod and a pentacle (dragon head is best) on the altar to increase the base power and recharge rate of the altar.

Craft a witches' cauldron.

It is used to craft items and liquids, cook, make stews, and prepare brews.
Make some liquid witchcraft.

Make ritual chalk.

Both used on its own and as a base for the other chalks.

Craft a goblet.

Place it on your altar to increase its power by 27 ME.

Make a filled goblet.

Place it on your altar to increase its power by 137 ME.

Craft a distillery.

It is used to make advanced fumes.

Craft a spinning wheel.

It is used to make magical strings and witches' attire.

Collect some spanish moss.

It is found in swampy areas and you need shears to harvest it.
Craft a poppet.
Craft a death protection poppet.

Make focal chalk.

This is the heart of any circle ritual.

Make fiery chalk.

Used for rituals of a more diabolic nature.

Make phasing chalk.

Used for rituals that require communications with other dimensions or across large areas.

Make bottled frostfire.

When placed, it can smelt iron ore or pulverized iron into cold iron when thrown in.

Summon a demon. Refer to the Codex Infernalis on how to do so.

Kill it with an athame to obtain its heart.

Craft a pentacle. 

Place it on your altar to increase the recharge rate to x4.

Craft a brazier.

Refer to the book of shadows for more information.

Craft an athame.

It is used to collect special crafting materials (e.g. hearts) by killing specific mobs.
Make some demonic elixer.
Craft the witches' attire set.

Make some elven frostfire.

These are used to make draconic cores.

Make some embergrass.

This plant will also spread.

Make some torchwood.

This plant will also spread.

Make some tallow.

It sees use in some brews and rituals, but is most commonly used in flying ointment and candles.

Craft the alchemist's attire set.

The alchemistâs attire gives you an extra potion from brewing, and reduces the effectiveness of negative effects applied though potions to you.

Craft the green witch attire set.

The green witches' attire improves healing when in nature.
Make some cloudy oil.
Make some fiery unguent and cleansing balm.
Make bottled hellfire.
Make otherwordly tears.
Get a bottle of blood.

Craft the besmirched attire.

The besmirched attire renders demonic mobs neutral to you and lets cast curses last longer.

After a higher demon has been summoned, they must be pledged to. This is done by wearing a full set of any witch robe variants, ingesting a stew of the grotesque and holding a certain other item in your offhand.

Craft a sigil table.

After a sigil has been made, it can be placed on solid blocks, or on dragonâs blood doors/chests/trapdoors, as well as on dragonâs blood brooms. They fade away after so long on normal blocks, but will stay forever on dragonâs blood doors/chests/trapdoors, until that block is broken, and will stay forever on dragonâs blood brooms.

Craft a white candle.

Place it on your altar to increase its power by 72 ME.
Make some draconium ingots.
Craft a draconic core.

Craft a dislocator.

It is first bound to a location by shift right-clicking. Right-clicking the dislocator will then teleport you to the bound location.
Craft a wyvern core.

Craft some wyvern fusion crafting injectors.

These are the second tier of fusion crafting injectors used in fusion crafting.
Craft a wyvern energy core by infusing a wyvern core with 10,000 mB of destabilized redstone in a fluid transposer.
Make an extreme crafting table.

Craft a fusion crafting core.

It is the center of the multi-block fusion crafting setup

Craft some basic fusion crafting injectors.

These are the first tier of fusion crafting injectors used in fusion crafting.
Craft a wyvern axe.
Craft a wyvern helm.
Craft a wyvern pickaxe.
Craft a wyvern shovel.
Craft a wyvern sword.
Craft a wyvern chestplate.
Craft wyvern leggings.
Craft wyvern boots.
Craft a draconic axe.
Craft a draconic pickaxe.
Craft a draconic shovel.
Craft a draconic sword.
Craft a wyvern bow.
Craft a draconic bow.
Craft some crystal matrix ingots.

Craft a draconic staff of power.

It has a max mining range of 7x7x7 along with the void junk option and the area of effect safe mode.
Craft a draconic helm.
Craft a draconic chestplate.
Craft draconic leggings.
Craft draconic boots.
Since the mob grinder can one-shot withers, you can make a wither farm.
Craft a mob grinder.
Craft some awakened draconium blocks.
Craft an awakened core.
Craft a draconic energy core.
Craft a draconic flux capacitor.

Max out your draconic armor and defeat the chaos guardian. Break the chaos crystal to obtain chaos shards.

Chaos islands spawn every 10,000 blocks in the End (e.g. x=10000, z=0 or x=10000, z=10000).
Craft a chaotic core.

Craft some draconic fusion crafting injectors.

These are the third tier of fusion crafting injectors used in fusion crafting.
Craft a crystal binder.

Craft some chaotic fusion crafting injectors.

These are the final tier of fusion crafting injectors used in fusion crafting.
Craft a draconic reactor core.
Craft a wyvern flux capacitor.
This upgrade key increases the recovery rate of draconic evolution armor shielding.
This upgrade key increases the capacity of draconic evolution armor shielding.

Craft an empty dimension tab.

These are used to create custom dimensions in the dimension enscriber.

Note: make an automatic ender dragon farm as you will need lots of dragon hearts.

Craft a dimension enscriber.

Use an empty dimension tab to enscribe a random dimension. You can also add dimlets to preset parts of your dimension.

Craft a dimension builder.

Use this to build a dimension once you've enscribed it.

Craft a matter receiver.

Bind a charged porter to it in order to teleport to it.

Craft a charged porter.

Bind it to a matter receiver and then right-click to teleport to it. RF charge is drained from the porter proportionally to the distance traveled.

Craft an advanced charged porter.

In addition to being capable of teleporting you across distance and dimension, the advanced charged porter can remember up to eight separate destinations.

Craft a matter transmitter and a dialing device.

The matter transmitter must be used in combination with a dialing device. When successfully dialed to a receiver, the transmitter will project a teleportation beam. By stepping into the beam, you are transmitted to the destination.

Craft a matter booster.

It consumes power to strengthen teleportation to an unpowered matter receiver - now you will take a small amount of damage but will not die when you teleport to a transmitter that has ran out of power.
Find some dimlet parcels.
Find some dimensional shard ore in dimensions you create.

Craft a machine infuser.

It is used to upgrade other machines by placing them into the infuser with dimensional shards.

Craft a destination analyzer.

When placed adjacent to a dialing device it allows you to see whether the spot you want to teleport to has run out of power or not. Can also be placed adjacent to a matter transmitter, the teleportation beam will then be tinted red if the destination is unsafe.

Craft a dimension editor.

It is used to change already created dimensions by inserting various dimlets.

Craft a dimlet workbench.

This allows you to deconstruct dimlets into individual parts and reconstruct new dimlets out of these parts.

Craft a Deep Dark portal.

Note: don't forget to bring torches.
Craft an angel ring.
Craft a turbine creative steam generator.
Craft a creative activation crystal.
Craft a cermonial blood orb.
Craft some warm blood.
Craft a creative sacrificial dagger.
Craft some blood tears.
Craft a neutronium ingot.
Craft some neutronium nuggets.
Craft some pile of neutrons.
Craft some ender silicon.
Craft some fire, air, earth and water gems.
Craft some everlasting stone.
Craft 4 golden singularities.

Craft a neutronium compressor.

This allows you to compress blocks into singularities.
Craft a creative modifier.
Craft a blessed stone.
Craft an infinity catalyst.

Craft a neutron collector.

Every 7111 ticks (about 6 minutes), one pile of neutrons will be fabricated.
Craft 4 iron singularities.
Craft 4 redstone singularities.
Craft 4 lapis singularities.
Craft a neutronium block.
Craft the everlasting guilty pool.
Congratulations ;)
Craft a creative satchel.
Craft a dried sponge.
Craft the adroysium armor set.
